Problem: The HR director wants a report showing how long employees have been with the company to plan loyalty bonuses.
Task: Calculate the total years of service for every employee (using their HireDate). Display their name and their rounded years of service.

SELECT
	Name,
	ROUND(DATEDIFF(YEAR, HireDate, CDate),0) AS Num_of_Years_in_service
FROM
	Employees
ORDER BY
	Num_of_Years_in_service DESC
